01:07:44,751 --> 01:07:47,276
No, l think you should go home.

965
01:07:48,255 --> 01:07:50,883
-He'll be home tomorrow, okay?
-Come on.

966
01:07:51,058 --> 01:07:53,288
Come on, honey. lt's gonna be okay.

967
01:07:57,264 --> 01:08:00,597
l was only fooling around.
l didn't mean for anyone to get hurt.

968
01:08:00,767 --> 01:08:01,825
Save it, Tara.

969
01:08:02,369 --> 01:08:06,169
Neither one of you had any business
being up on that ladder.

970
01:08:06,340 --> 01:08:08,308
Do you see why the rules are in place?

971
01:08:08,475 --> 01:08:10,636
We just talked about horsing around,
remember?

972
01:08:10,811 --> 01:08:14,076
Yes. l'm really upset.

973
01:08:15,182 --> 01:08:17,150
l'm so sorry.

974
01:08:18,118 --> 01:08:19,415
What am l gonna do with you?

975
01:08:19,586 --> 01:08:23,818
l gotta separate you in class,
and l gotta separate you in swimming too?

976
01:08:23,991 --> 01:08:28,360
Tara, you're on towel duty
for the rest of the season.

977
01:08:28,528 --> 01:08:30,393
-Do l still get to swim?
-Yes.

978
01:08:30,564 --> 01:08:32,464
After each and every meet and practice...

979
01:08:32,633 --> 01:08:36,592
...you'll be responsible
for all the wet and dirty towels.

980
01:08:36,770 --> 01:08:38,203
What about her?

981
01:08:39,673 --> 01:08:41,573
-Chrissa.
-lt's okay.

982
01:08:41,742 --> 01:08:43,334
l decided l'm gonna quit the team.

983
01:08:44,144 --> 01:08:46,044
Chrissa, that isn't necessary.

984
01:08:46,213 --> 01:08:49,080
Now, Chrissa, l know you're upset
about your brother...

985
01:08:49,249 --> 01:08:52,343
...but there have to be consequences
when you break the rules.

986
01:08:52,519 --> 01:08:54,680
l'm not quitting
just to get out of punishment.

987
01:08:56,857 --> 01:08:58,347
Okay, then, why?

988
01:09:07,467 --> 01:09:09,230
Okay, Chrissa.

989
01:09:09,403 --> 01:09:12,964
You're gonna be cleaning up the classroom
for the next two weeks.

990
01:09:20,981 --> 01:09:22,608
Bring it on. Bring it on.

991
01:09:22,783 --> 01:09:24,944
Yeah, you don't want me to bring it on.

992
01:09:25,118 --> 01:09:26,312
Tyler.

993
01:09:26,486 --> 01:09:28,954
-We have something for you.
-Yes, we do.

994
01:09:29,523 --> 01:09:31,457
What? A pound of chocolate Raisinets?

995
01:09:31,625 --> 01:09:33,525
-No.
-No.

996
01:09:33,694 --> 01:09:36,925
-A new Game Boy?
-No.

997
01:09:37,097 --> 01:09:38,724
Then what?

998
01:09:40,467 --> 01:09:45,029
-A solidarity scarf, silly.
-Sweet.

999
01:09:46,640 --> 01:09:49,131
No way am l wearing this.

1000
01:09:50,644 --> 01:09:51,838
Dig it.

1001
01:09:52,779 --> 01:09:55,145
Lemonade and cookies in the kitchen.

1002
01:09:55,615 --> 01:09:57,344
-l'm totally there.
-Do you want some?

1003
01:09:57,517 --> 01:09:59,109
Sure, but wait.

1004
01:10:02,356 --> 01:10:04,256
l heard you quit the swim team.

1005
01:10:04,424 --> 01:10:06,449
-Well, yeah. l had to.
-Why?

1006
01:10:06,626 --> 01:10:08,719
Because you're out
for the rest of the season.

1007
01:10:08,895 --> 01:10:11,591
-So l'm gonna stay out too.
-Well, that's stupid.

1008
01:10:12,532 --> 01:10:16,764
Tyler, l'm really, really sorry
this happened to you.

1009
01:10:16,937 --> 01:10:19,269
Me too. l'm never listening to Tara again.

1010
01:10:20,507 --> 01:10:21,804
This is all my fault.

1011
01:10:21,975 --> 01:10:25,308
Chrissa, it isn't about you.
l should have never listened to her.

1012
01:10:25,479 --> 01:10:30,507
No. No, if Tara didn't hate me so much,
she would have never done this to you.

1013
01:10:30,684 --> 01:10:33,414
-l don't wanna be around her anymore.
-So you're a quitter?

1014
01:10:34,521 --> 01:10:36,352
l guess so.

1015
01:10:56,710 --> 01:10:59,873
The Tigers will be inspired to win
after they see this poster.

1016
01:11:00,047 --> 01:11:01,947
l hope so.

1017
01:11:02,649 --> 01:11:04,241
So...

1018
01:11:05,352 --> 01:11:07,343
...l hear you quit the swim team.

1019
01:11:09,089 --> 01:11:11,523
Yeah, l decided
l don't really like swimming.

1020
01:11:11,691 --> 01:11:12,988
Really?

1021
01:11:13,160 --> 01:11:15,720
And if Tyler can't swim....

1022
01:11:15,896 --> 01:11:19,195
l don't think this has anything to do
with Tyler.

1023
01:11:19,366 --> 01:11:23,234
l do, however, think
this has something to do with Tara.

1024
01:11:27,207 --> 01:11:28,868
You know...

1025
01:11:30,143 --> 01:11:32,111
...l always felt sorry for Tara.

1026
01:11:33,213 --> 01:11:34,237
Why?

1027
01:11:34,414 --> 01:11:37,349
Well, because when someone
is determined...

1028
01:11:37,517 --> 01:11:40,384
...to make other people
feel bad about themselves...

1029
01:11:40,554 --> 01:11:43,614
...it's usually so they can feel good
about themselves.

1030
01:11:44,925 --> 01:11:47,359
How can making someone feel bad
make you feel good?

1031
01:11:47,928 --> 01:11:51,523
Because in order to feel
like you're worth something...

1032
01:11:51,698 --> 01:11:55,600
...you need other people
to feel less than their best.

1033
01:11:55,769 --> 01:12:00,433
lt sounds to me
like that's what Tara's done to you.

1034
01:12:04,311 --> 01:12:06,609
She doesn't act like she feels bad
about herself.

1035
01:12:06,780 --> 01:12:10,511
Saying mean things.
Hurting other people.

1036
01:12:10,684 --> 01:12:12,845
Cutting you down.

1037
01:12:13,854 --> 01:12:15,617
She must be very insecure.

1038
01:12:18,925 --> 01:12:22,452
lf you could wave a magic wand
and change something...

1039
01:12:22,629 --> 01:12:24,756
...what would you do?

1040
01:12:27,267 --> 01:12:29,132
<i>You won't be able to do it, chicken,</i>

1041
01:12:29,302 --> 01:12:31,429
<i>Tara, get down,</i>

1042
01:12:33,106 --> 01:12:35,074
l would take back Tyler's accident...

1043
01:12:35,242 --> 01:12:37,904
...and make it so that no one's ever mean
to anyone again.

1044
01:12:38,078 --> 01:12:43,141
That would be lovely, wouldn't it?
But it's not very realistic.

1045
01:12:44,184 --> 01:12:47,517
l find that sometimes
when kids have a big problem...

1046
01:12:47,687 --> 01:12:50,952
...they try to solve it themselves...

1047
01:12:51,625 --> 01:12:56,358
...but sometimes problems
are too big and complicated...

1048
01:12:56,530 --> 01:12:59,465
...for kids to solve on their own.

1049
01:12:59,933 --> 01:13:03,699
They need help and they need to know
that it's okay to ask for help.

1050
01:13:03,870 --> 01:13:07,203
Grownups say that,
but what if it doesn't work?

1051
01:13:07,374 --> 01:13:11,435
We're the ones who have to go to school
with the mean kids who just get meaner.

1052
01:13:12,379 --> 01:13:14,347
l see your point...

1053
01:13:14,514 --> 01:13:16,175
...but l think you'd be surprised...

1054
01:13:16,349 --> 01:13:18,681
...at how turning to an adult you trust
can help.

1055
01:13:19,553 --> 01:13:26,049
Sometimes they can help in a way
where it's not really obvious.

1056
01:13:26,526 --> 01:13:29,495
Don't you have an adult you can turn to
when you have a problem?

1057
01:13:31,932 --> 01:13:34,196
My mom says l can tell her and my dad
anything.

1058
01:13:34,734 --> 01:13:36,964
That would be a very good place to start.

1059
01:13:43,210 --> 01:13:44,871
Thanks.

1060
01:13:52,586 --> 01:13:55,214
Don't spoil your appetite.
Oh, hey, Chrissa.

1061
01:13:55,956 --> 01:13:59,119
Chicken Fricassee's on the menu.
With paprika? Without?

1062
01:13:59,292 --> 01:14:00,384
-With.
-With.

1063
01:14:00,560 --> 01:14:01,686
-Mom.
-Hand me that.

1064
01:14:01,861 --> 01:14:03,556
-Dad?
-Yeah.

1065
01:14:05,699 --> 01:14:08,031
Moving out here has been really hard.

1066
01:14:08,201 --> 01:14:09,998
Because you miss your friends?

1067
01:14:10,170 --> 01:14:14,766
Not just because of that,
but because of this.

1068
01:14:18,345 --> 01:14:19,539
Oh, Chrissa.

1069
01:14:22,082 --> 01:14:24,346
May l see that? Let me see.

1070
01:14:26,886 --> 01:14:28,376
Do you know who did this?

1071
01:14:28,555 --> 01:14:31,888
-l'm betting it was Tara.
-Swim-team Tara?

1072
01:14:32,492 --> 01:14:33,516
Yeah.

1073
01:14:33,693 --> 01:14:36,253
lt's because of her
that she quit the team.

1074
01:14:36,429 --> 01:14:38,056
Chrissa, you quit the swim team?

1075
01:14:38,231 --> 01:14:41,564
Honey, l'm so sorry.
That Tara is bad news.

1076
01:14:42,168 --> 01:14:44,363
l knew something was going on.

1077
01:14:45,872 --> 01:14:48,739
lt's just so hard.
l've been trying to make it work.

1078
01:14:48,908 --> 01:14:50,398
Oh, sweetheart, for how long?

1079
01:14:51,945 --> 01:14:53,435
Since the first day of school.

1080
01:14:53,613 --> 01:14:55,911
So Gwen wasn't the only one
being bullied?

1081
01:14:56,883 --> 01:14:59,317
Oh, honey, l wish you'd come to us.

1082
01:14:59,486 --> 01:15:01,886
l don't wanna be called a tattletale.

1083
01:15:02,055 --> 01:15:05,582
Tattling's different.
lt's kind of like getting even with someone.

1084
01:15:05,759 --> 01:15:07,750
Speaking up is protecting yourself.

1085
01:15:07,927 --> 01:15:10,157
l'm so sorry this has been going on.

1086
01:15:10,330 --> 01:15:14,198
Believe me, it stops now.
l'm gonna call the principal and Mr. Beck.

1087
01:15:14,367 --> 01:15:16,335
We're gonna set up a meeting
and tell them.

1088
01:15:16,503 --> 01:15:18,903
No, that's just gonna make it worse.

1089
01:15:19,072 --> 01:15:21,438
Sweetie, that's how bullies work.

1090
01:15:21,608 --> 01:15:24,099
They depend on kids being
too afraid to speak up.

1091
01:15:24,277 --> 01:15:27,144
That's how the bullying keeps going.

1092
01:15:28,481 --> 01:15:31,348
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

1093
01:15:31,651 --> 01:15:35,644
-Are you sure, Mom?
-l'm positive, baby.

1094
01:15:35,822 --> 01:15:37,289
Okay.

1095
01:15:37,991 --> 01:15:39,788
Oh, hey.

1096
01:15:39,959 --> 01:15:44,123
Are you still working on ideas for
that big fourth-grade social studies project?

1097
01:15:44,631 --> 01:15:45,757
Yeah.

1098
01:15:47,067 --> 01:15:49,262
Maybe there's something
we could do about that.

1099
01:15:50,203 --> 01:15:52,171
Okay, class, let's open our English books.

1100
01:15:52,339 --> 01:15:54,364
-Mr. Beck?
-To page 50.

1101
01:15:54,541 --> 01:15:56,304
-Mr. Beck.
-Yes, Chrissa?

1102
01:15:57,944 --> 01:15:59,775
l have an idea for our project.

1103
01:16:00,146 --> 01:16:01,704
Well, l love your enthusiasm...

1104
01:16:01,881 --> 01:16:03,781
...but we're talking about that
next week.

1105
01:16:03,950 --> 01:16:05,815
-But l have an idea today.
-What?

1106
01:16:05,985 --> 01:16:08,317
-Have a llama-bean omelet this morning?
-Tara.

1107
01:16:11,524 --> 01:16:12,718
Okay, Chrissa, what is it?

1108
01:16:12,892 --> 01:16:15,360
Let's do our project
about school bullying.

1109
01:16:16,663 --> 01:16:18,790
l think that's a great idea.

1110
01:16:19,165 --> 01:16:21,065
How many of you have felt bullied?

1111
01:16:28,942 --> 01:16:31,376
l wanna do this
because this happened to me.

1112
01:16:31,544 --> 01:16:33,842
And l didn't know how to make it stop.

1113
01:16:34,013 --> 01:16:36,743
And then l didn't even
wanna go to school.

1114
01:16:52,699 --> 01:16:55,497
Okay. Looks like we have a project.

1115
01:17:09,082 --> 01:17:10,777
So?

1116
01:17:10,950 --> 01:17:13,350
You don't have to ask. School was great.

1117
01:17:13,520 --> 01:17:15,044
They loved my idea.

1118
01:17:15,221 --> 01:17:17,849
You know what?
Lots of kids have been bullied.

1119
01:17:18,024 --> 01:17:20,458
Did Tara or Jayden
do anything bad today?

1120
01:17:20,994 --> 01:17:22,825
No.

1121
01:17:22,996 --> 01:17:25,863
See? l knew you
were gonna have a good day.

1122
01:17:30,670 --> 01:17:32,934
So tomorrow's the big swim meet,
isn't it?

1123
01:17:34,007 --> 01:17:36,100
Yeah, l guess it is.

1124
01:17:37,477 --> 01:17:38,876
l decided l'm not gonna go.

1125
01:17:41,314 --> 01:17:43,908
Did l ever tell you
how the kids were mean to me?

1126
01:17:44,083 --> 01:17:45,573
You, Mom?

1127
01:17:45,752 --> 01:17:47,583
Yup.

1128
01:17:47,754 --> 01:17:53,590
l was getting the highest grades in the class
and the kids were calling me names...

1129
01:17:53,760 --> 01:17:57,628
...like ''egghead'' and ''brainiac''
and ''bookworm.''

1130
01:17:57,797 --> 01:17:59,162
''Miss Square.''

1131
01:18:00,366 --> 01:18:04,393
So to make it stop,
l started failing instead of succeeding.

1132
01:18:04,971 --> 01:18:07,303
And then l realized how stupid that was.

1133
01:18:07,474 --> 01:18:09,101
Why?

1134
01:18:09,909 --> 01:18:12,969
Sweetie, it's never smart
to be less than who you are.

1135
01:18:13,413 --> 01:18:16,780
Or to let anyone
take anything away from you.

1136
01:18:18,284 --> 01:18:19,945
Thanks, Mom.

1137
01:18:23,156 --> 01:18:24,418
Jimmy.

1138
01:18:24,591 --> 01:18:26,218
Wait up.

1139
01:18:31,264 --> 01:18:33,562
-Chrissa.
-Hey.

1140
01:18:33,733 --> 01:18:36,167
Well, looks like
our team's complete, guys.

1141
01:18:36,803 --> 01:18:38,771
Welcome back, Chrissa.

1142
01:18:40,473 --> 01:18:42,338
Go, Chrissa.

1143
01:18:42,509 --> 01:18:45,945
-Good to have you back, sweetie.
-Come on, get out here, we're warming up.

1144
01:18:48,715 --> 01:18:50,876
Now we have a team.

1145
01:18:51,050 --> 01:18:52,312
-Chrissa.
-Go, Chrissa.

1146
01:18:56,022 --> 01:18:59,355
-<i>Next race: girls 50-meter freestyle,</i>
-Go, go, go.

1147
01:19:03,062 --> 01:19:04,825
Go, go, go.

1148
01:19:04,998 --> 01:19:07,865
-Go, go, go.
-<i>Swimmers, take your mark,</i>

1149
01:19:08,034 --> 01:19:10,332
-Come on, Chrissa.
-Okay, Chrissa, let's go!

1150
01:19:11,404 --> 01:19:12,564
Do it, sweetie.

1151
01:19:19,746 --> 01:19:21,145
Go, go, go!

1152
01:19:25,218 --> 01:19:26,242
Go!

1153
01:19:26,419 --> 01:19:29,388
Let's go, come on, come on!

1154
01:19:31,057 --> 01:19:32,922
Come on, Chrissa!

1155
01:19:35,495 --> 01:19:38,726
Come on, let's go, let's go, let's go!

1156
01:19:46,573 --> 01:19:49,007
Come on, Chrissa, go!

1157
01:19:50,310 --> 01:19:52,972
Come on, go, go, go!

1158
01:19:53,913 --> 01:19:56,541
Come on, come on!

1159
01:19:57,350 --> 01:19:58,942
Go, go!

1160
01:20:04,123 --> 01:20:07,786
Go! Come on, Chrissa!

1161
01:20:10,763 --> 01:20:12,287
Attagirl, pull!

1162
01:20:17,870 --> 01:20:24,241
<i>Chrissa Maxwell wins</i>
<i>the 50-meter freestyle for the Tigers,</i>

1163
01:20:24,644 --> 01:20:26,942
-Yes!
-Yeah.

1164
01:20:27,113 --> 01:20:30,571
<i>Next race: boys 50-meter freestyle,</i>

1165
01:20:30,750 --> 01:20:31,774
-<i>Swimmers,</i>
-Thanks.

1166
01:20:32,285 --> 01:20:33,616
<i>Take your mark,</i>

1167
01:20:43,162 --> 01:20:45,653
Tara. Tara.

1168
01:20:45,832 --> 01:20:47,060
What?

1169
01:20:47,767 --> 01:20:51,533
We may never be best friends,
we may never be any kind of friends...

1170
01:20:51,704 --> 01:20:53,501
...but that's okay.

1171
01:20:53,673 --> 01:20:55,436
You and l are the best swimmers.

1172
01:20:55,608 --> 01:20:58,441
And if we work together,
our team could win.

1173
01:21:00,146 --> 01:21:04,082
<i>James Spencer wins the 50-meter freestyle</i>
<i>for the Tigers,,,</i>

1174
01:21:05,451 --> 01:21:06,975
<i>,,,and ties the score,</i>

1175
01:21:08,621 --> 01:21:11,419
<i>Coming up, our last race of the day:</i>

1176
01:21:11,591 --> 01:21:14,651
-<i>The girls 200-meter medley relay,</i>
-Come on.

1177
01:21:19,399 --> 01:21:21,367
Chrissa, you're first, Alexandra second...

1178
01:21:21,534 --> 01:21:23,434
...Rachel third, and,
Tara, you're anchor.

1179
01:21:23,603 --> 01:21:25,093
-Mr. Beck?
-Yeah?

1180
01:21:25,405 --> 01:21:27,168
Chrissa should swim anchor.

1181
01:21:27,340 --> 01:21:29,103
But l've never swam anchor before.

1182
01:21:29,275 --> 01:21:30,640
Are you kidding me?

1183
01:21:30,810 --> 01:21:33,506
You're the strongest swimmer.
You're like a human fish.

1184
01:21:33,846 --> 01:21:35,143
-But l don't know--
-Come on.

1185
01:21:35,314 --> 01:21:38,545
Do you want this team to win or not?

1186
01:21:39,686 --> 01:21:43,122
Yes. Come on, come on, come on.
Let's go, let's go.

1187
01:21:43,289 --> 01:21:44,483
-Come on, Tara.
-Come on.

1188
01:21:44,657 --> 01:21:46,056
-Come on, Tara.
-Come on, Tara.

1189
01:21:46,225 --> 01:21:47,749
You can do it.

1190
01:21:49,696 --> 01:21:52,460
<i>Swimmers, on your mark,</i>

1191
01:21:55,668 --> 01:21:59,126
-Come on!
-Come on, Tara!

1192
01:21:59,305 --> 01:22:00,397
Go, Tara! Come on.

1193
01:22:01,374 --> 01:22:02,534
Let's go, Tara.

1194
01:22:04,110 --> 01:22:05,338
Tara!

1195
01:22:05,511 --> 01:22:07,138
Go, go, come on!

1196
01:22:07,313 --> 01:22:09,076
Go, Tara.

1197
01:22:09,916 --> 01:22:11,645
-Go, Tara!
-Come on!

1198
01:22:12,385 --> 01:22:15,183
Come on, Tara, go!

1199
01:22:15,354 --> 01:22:18,949
Keep going, keep going!
Come on, Tara! Come on!

1200
01:22:19,125 --> 01:22:20,217
Let's go, Tara!

1201
01:22:28,267 --> 01:22:30,599
Slow down, Tara.

1202
01:22:30,837 --> 01:22:31,929
Let's go!

1203
01:22:34,707 --> 01:22:35,731
Go, Tara, go!

1204
01:22:35,908 --> 01:22:38,240
