Come on, Alexandra!

1207
01:22:49,856 --> 01:22:52,188
Go, Alexandra!

1208
01:22:57,964 --> 01:23:00,432
Come on! Go, Alexandra!

1209
01:23:05,138 --> 01:23:07,572
-Come on, Alexandra.
-Pull!

1210
01:23:11,444 --> 01:23:13,776
-You can do it!
-Come on! Go, go, go!

1211
01:23:13,946 --> 01:23:15,140
Please, go! Go!

1212
01:23:17,917 --> 01:23:18,975
Come on, come on!

1213
01:23:25,858 --> 01:23:28,588
Let's go, Alexandra, come on.

1214
01:23:29,162 --> 01:23:31,960
Come on, Rachel!
Go, Tigers, come on!

1215
01:23:39,906 --> 01:23:41,806
Come on, Rachel.

1216
01:23:41,974 --> 01:23:43,839
Go! Go, go!

1217
01:23:44,944 --> 01:23:46,002
Yeah, Rachel!

1218
01:23:46,746 --> 01:23:47,770
Good job.

1219
01:23:48,648 --> 01:23:50,138
You can catch her.

1220
01:23:50,316 --> 01:23:51,340
Go, Rachel, go!

1221
01:23:51,517 --> 01:23:53,246
Go!

1222
01:23:53,786 --> 01:23:54,844
Come on, Rachel!

1223
01:23:55,021 --> 01:23:57,581
Go, Tigers! Come on! Come on.

1224
01:23:57,757 --> 01:24:00,351
Okay, don't overreach,
it'll make your back arch.

1225
01:24:00,526 --> 01:24:02,255
Keep your fingers open, not clenched.

1226
01:24:02,428 --> 01:24:05,192
You're going to have to
bend your elbows sooner underwater.

1227
01:24:05,364 --> 01:24:06,831
lf you do that, we're gonna win.

1228
01:24:06,999 --> 01:24:10,435
Come on, Rachel! Go, Tigers! Come on!

1229
01:24:18,978 --> 01:24:20,969
Go, Chrissa!

1230
01:24:24,050 --> 01:24:25,381
Come on, you can do it!

1231
01:24:25,685 --> 01:24:27,550
Go! Go!

1232
01:24:34,026 --> 01:24:35,687
Go, go, go! Come on!

1233
01:24:40,333 --> 01:24:43,234
Chrissa! You can do it!

1234
01:24:44,737 --> 01:24:47,797
You're second! Touch it! Yeah!

1235
01:24:56,215 --> 01:24:59,275
-Come on!
-Come on, Chrissa. Come on.

1236
01:25:22,441 --> 01:25:26,400
l'm very, very proud
of this year's fourth-grade project.

1237
01:25:26,846 --> 01:25:30,441
And it will stand here at the school
as a permanent reminder.

1238
01:25:33,920 --> 01:25:37,617
Here to present our project
is Miss Chrissa Maxwell.

1239
01:25:37,790 --> 01:25:39,758
-Chrissa!
-Hi.

1240
01:25:41,761 --> 01:25:43,353
Go, Chrissa.

1241
01:25:43,529 --> 01:25:45,429
Our project is on school bullying.

1242
01:25:45,598 --> 01:25:48,123
Kids who've been bullied
are afraid to speak out...

1243
01:25:48,301 --> 01:25:50,166
...because the bullying might get worse.

1244
01:25:50,336 --> 01:25:52,827
They think there's nothing
that they can do about it.

1245
01:25:53,005 --> 01:25:56,065
l know this from personal experience.

1246
01:25:56,242 --> 01:26:00,303
But if they stop and speak up,
things can get a lot better.

1247
01:26:01,647 --> 01:26:04,241
Never keep bullying a secret.

1248
01:26:04,750 --> 01:26:08,413
Whether it's about you or a friend.

1249
01:26:09,288 --> 01:26:13,088
This is the friendship arch, and
everyone in the fourth grade chose a word.

1250
01:26:13,259 --> 01:26:15,352
And in the middle
there's the word ''hello'' ...

1251
01:26:15,528 --> 01:26:20,261
...because my grandmother always told me,
'''Hello' is the first word in a friendship.''

1252
01:26:20,566 --> 01:26:22,466
l love you, Nana.

1253
01:26:24,437 --> 01:26:28,771
l chose the word ''courage'' because
it takes courage to stand up to a bully.

1254
01:26:29,508 --> 01:26:32,568
And it takes courage to stop being a bully.

1255
01:26:34,947 --> 01:26:36,744
''Accept'' is my word.

1256
01:26:36,916 --> 01:26:39,009
And l realized that it starts with me.

1257
01:26:39,318 --> 01:26:42,947
No one is better or worse
than anyone else.

1258
01:26:43,122 --> 01:26:46,649
We all have the same problems.
l love you, Mom.

1259
01:26:47,493 --> 01:26:50,087
l chose the word ''forgive.''

1260
01:26:50,262 --> 01:26:52,822
Once you forgive, you can move forward.

1261
01:26:54,533 --> 01:26:56,091
l chose the word ''strength'' ...

1262
01:26:56,268 --> 01:26:58,532
...because no matter
what's going on around you...

1263
01:26:58,704 --> 01:27:00,467
...it's important to be strong inside.

1264
01:27:00,639 --> 01:27:03,665
And to be true to yourself.

1265
01:27:03,943 --> 01:27:05,467
l chose the word ''kind.''

1266
01:27:05,644 --> 01:27:08,135
l chose the words ''no envy.''

1267
01:27:08,848 --> 01:27:10,611
l chose the word ''loyal.''

1268
01:27:27,033 --> 01:27:30,230
Come on, Amanda.
We're taking Starburst for her first swim.

